The paper focuses on the use of convolutional neural networks for image classification and segmentation, specifically in the context of recognizing materials within glass vessels. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a new approach for focusing the attention of the net on a specific region of interest, which could be considered a form of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a new data set, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) or multimedia (cs.MM).
